CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 15, 1941, pg. 22 reads: "Matron's Club Installs Officers - The Progressive Matrons club installed officers last week as a result of a recent annual election. The new personnel includes, first row, left to right: Mrs. Inez Rose, reporter; Mrs. James E. Smith, president; Mrs. Lena Carter, financial secretary.  The second row show: Mrs. Georgia Brown, vice-president; Mrs. Wesley Irons, treasurer; Mrs. Elizabeth Smart, mistress of the social sessions.  in third row are: Mrs. Naomi G. Walker, Mrs. Ellen Turner, recording secretary; Mrs. Marie Robinson, assistant to the mistress of social sessions.  Mrs. Walker installed the officers. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Progressive Matrons club officers first row from left: reporter Inez Rose, president Mrs. James E. Smith, financial secretary Lena Carter; second row: vice-presient Georgia Brown, treasurer Mrs. Wesley Irons, Elizabeth Smart; third row: Naomi G. Walker, Ellen Turner, and Marie Robinson, posed in domestic interior with floral wallpaper, mantle, and floor lamp with light colored shade, another version
